{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d78011d9-5803-4e7a-aa37-1e67f50b5d68","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. MSTest v3 requires **.NET 6+** for .NET Core targets and **.NET Framework 4.6.2+** for desktop. Your project has two problematic TFMs:\n\n| Target | Status |\n|---|---|\n| `net462` | ✅ Supported |\n| `net5.0` | ❌ Not supported (needs `net6.0`+) |\n| `netcoreapp3.1` | ❌ Not supported (needs `net6.0`+) |\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to:\n\n1. **Update TFMs** — replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with `net6.0` or later (both are EOL anyway).\n2. **Update packages** — MSTest v3 consolidates into a single `MSTest` package, replacing `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`.\n3. **Review breaking changes** — some assertions, attributes, and initialization behaviors changed in v3.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1e001568-23d6-4796-a96e-14743e2036f6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Let me provide accurate information about compatibility issues.\n\nMSTest v3 key changes:\n- Minimum supported frameworks: .NET 6+ and .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n- `net5.0` is NOT supported (it's EOL and MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+)\n- `netcoreapp3.1` is NOT supported (MSTest v3 requires .NET 6+)\n- `net462` should still be supported (MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+)\n\n\n- MSTest v3 consolidated the packages into a single meta-package, though the individual packages are still available if needed.","outputTokens":481,"requestId":"0423:C1158:23D6F3B:2871697:69E83214"},"id":"f57b81de-c7f0-4ee4-9cc3-a52e5e198e60","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:27:42.459Z","parentId":"d23f9266-1bff-4a11-84ec-bfbafc7ff409"}
